%description:
Test that the simulation exits gracefully if there's an error while building the network.
 - exit code must be 1 (not zero and different from crash exit code):
 - nothing should be printed after "End run..." message and the error message (Note "$")

%file: test.ned
network Test {
    types:
        module Node { gates: inout g; }
    submodules:
        node[5]: Node;
    connections:
        node[1].g <--> node[1000].g;    
}

%exitcode: 1

%contains-regex: stdout
<!> Error in module \(Test\) Test: No submodule `node\[1000\]' to be connected, at test\.ned:7\.


End run of OMNeT\+\+$

%contains-regex: stderr
^$
